org.mindswap.owls.process.variable
Interface ValueOf

All Superinterfaces:
OWLEntity, OWLIndividual, OWLObject, OWLValue, ParameterValue, Visitable<ParameterValueVisitor,ParameterValue>
All Known Implementing Classes:
ValueOfImpl
public interface ValueOf
extends ParameterValue, OWLIndividual

Used to describe the source of a value (to be assigned to a Parameter specified by a Binding). The source may refer either to a Parameter of another process (encapsulated by a Perform) within the same composite process, to a Loc, or to a Existential within this composite process, i.e., if a Loc or Existential is referenced the perform must be OWLS.Process#ThisPerform.

getParameter

Parameter getParameter()
Get the source process variable viewed as a Parameter. This method should only be used if it is known that the variable is a Input or Output.

Returns:
The source process variable viewed as Parameter. null if this property is missing or the process variable is neither an Input nor Output.

getTheVar

ProcessVar getTheVar()
Get the source process variable. This method should be used if it is unknown whether the variable is actually a Input, Output, or Loc.

Returns:
The source process variable viewed as a general ProcessVar. null if this property is missing.

setSource

void setSource(Parameter param,
               Perform perform)
Set the source parameter reference and from which perform it comes. Removes possibly existing previous source process variable reference, independent of whether it is a Parameter or Loc reference.

Parameters:
param - The source parameter.
perform - The source perform. Note that the perform must be within the enclosing composite process, i.e., the perform must not be beyond scope.

setSource

void setSource(Loc local)
Set the source local variable and implicitly set the source perform to OWLS.Process#ThisPerform, since only local variables of this composite process can be referred. (This is implied by the scope of local variables.)

Parameters:
local - The source local variable (declared in the enclosing composite process).

setSource

void setSource(Existential existential)
Set the source existential variable and implicitly set the source perform to OWLS.Process#ThisPerform, since only local variables of this composite process can be referred. (This is implied by the scope of existential variables.)

Parameters:
existential - The source existential variable (declared in the enclosing composite process).
